HEADWORD: Ephemera
<hw>E*phem"e*ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ a day fly, fr. <?/ daily, lasting but a day; <?/ over + <?/
day.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A fever of one day's
continuance only.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>A genus of insects including
the day flies, or ephemeral flies. See <cref>Ephemeral fly</cref>, under
<er>Ephemeral</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ephemeral</ent>⟦br⟧
